result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler C. Tuttle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:29 am case called. Defendant Tyler C. Tuttle in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Tyler C. Tuttle in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court goes over file and questions counsel. ADA Anderson makes statement regarding resolution and states on the record. State moves to amend Count 3 to Misd. Bail Jumping in violation of 946.49(1)(a). Attorney Szilagyi concurs.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Court accepts the amendment of the State of Count 3 to Misd. Bail Jumping.  Plea: No Contest to Count 2 & Count 3. Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Court dismissed and reads in Counts 1 & 4. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: Count 2-Impose 30 days WCJ, Count 3-90 Days WCJ, Both STAYED and placed on probation for a 1 year. If revoked with Huber and Good time Credit. No credit for time served. Concurrent to each other but consecutive to any sentence existing at the time of revocation. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through,  maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.Terms of Agent, Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights Given.
